n.  The system did crash a few times while I was playing it, but the Microsoft reps explained that it wasn't running on true hardware, and I haven't seen one crash on my nieces X-Box.  As for multiplayer support, that doesn't really impress me.. PC gaming online is all I'd do because I don't wanna pay extra for their networks when most gaming over the net is free if you have a cable modem.  Finally as far as graphics go, I've never really seen anything that blows me away.  PS2 can go screw itself.  Its only the most popular system because of sheep.  It's the &quot;cool&quot; gamers system. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=127902">Jaeron -Shadowstalker</a>, Merc for Hire, at your service. 
